This paper focuses on improving the ability of robots to grasp objects, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also utilizes deep neural networks for grasp detection, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper introduces a novel loss function and scorer, which are both related to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed model using a simulated grasp trial criterion, which is related to control systems (cs.SY).
